added.title: Cat's Fancy
added.description: Robin decides to become a cat so that Starfire will finally love him.

added.title: Leg Day
added.description: After being defeated due to poor leg strength, Raven and the Titans work out their lower bodies and become the League of Legs.

added.title: Dignity of Teeth
added.description: When Beast Boy gets a stack of cash from the Tooth Fairy, against Raven's advice the other Titans start knocking out their own teeth to get some of that sweet Tooth Fairy money.

added.title: Croissant
added.description: A giant cocoon mysteriously appears in the Titans' living room, and no one can find Beast Boy.

added.title: Spice Game
added.description: Tired of Robin's bland cooking, the other Titans try their hand at spicing up their food.

added.title: Mr. Butt
added.description: After Starfire is set up by Blackfire and sent to prison, the Titans work to make Blackfire a better sister while Starfire plots her revenge.

added.title: Man Person
added.description: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.

added.title: Pirates
added.description: When Aqualad and Raven fall for each other, Beast Boy fights this match - with intensity.

added.title: Money Grandma
added.description: When Robin starts a smear campaign against the other Titans so that he can be reelected Team Leader, Raven brings in a great leader from the past to teach Robin a thing or two.

added.title: Brian
added.description: When The Brain captures the Titans to fuel Project B.R.I.A.N., the Titan's little buddies are the only heroes who can save them.

added.title: Salty Codgers
added.description: Raven is delighted when the other Titans are magically turned into old people during a battle.

added.title: I See You
added.description: Robin brings Starfire on a fake stakeout in an attempt to get a kiss, while Cyborg and Beast Boy hold their own stakeout to discover Raven's dark secret.

added.title: Nature
added.description: In order to get his powers back, Beast Boy returns to nature and finds it much harsher than he expects.

added.title: Knowledge
added.description: Starfire wants to learn more, but will knowledge make her a bummer?

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: The Titans throw a slumber party to help Cyborg get over his fear of Scary Teri.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Dad is in charge of getting the kids to their first day back at school on time, but he's overslept and now he can't find Gumball, Darwin or Anais anywhere. He sets about retracing his steps from the day before to work out where they might be.

added.title: The Nemesis
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover that Rob, who once swore to wreak vengeance on them, has been trying to destroy them for some time but his traps never work. Taking pity on him, the kids make it their mission to help Rob become a better nemesis. But they do their job too well, creating a super-villain they may not be able to control.

added.title: The Crew
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin decide it's time they join a crew, they agree that the coolest posse in Elmore is the Senior Citizens. They do everything they can to fit in with them, going to extraordinary lengths to prove themselves worthy of running (well, walking very slowly) with them.

added.title: The Others
added.description: When Anais reveals that she's in the grade above them at school, Gumball and Darwin's eyes are suddenly opened to a whole new world of other students at Elmore Junior High. Gumball is horrified to learn that there are a bunch of characters who are barely aware of his existence and is determined to force his way into their lives.

added.title: The Signature
added.description: Dad discovers that Granny Jojo and Louie are planning to get married and move to Florida. To stop this happening he adopts Louie so that he can forbid him from marrying Granny Jojo. But this triggers a series of adoptions within the family which quickly spirals out of control, and causes the unexpected return of someone from Dad's past.

added.title: The Coach
added.description: The new coach at Elmore High stands up to Jamie. The new Coach witnesses Jamie bullying the other kids at lunch and steps in. Jamie is made to apologise, much to the amazement of the other kids. Gumball and Darwin worry about Jamie seeking revenge, especially when they see him sneaking into the back of Coach's car. They use their newly acquired gym skills to save the Coach from being bullied.

added.title: The Joy
added.description: Miss Simian has to save herself from a contagious Joy virus infecting the whole school. After Dad gives Gumball and Darwin a special hug, the kids go to school filled with a virulent form of Joy. Miss Simian quickly identifies the terrible affliction, and soon enough it spreads to the other kids. She has to find a cure before it's too late. Before Ms Simian herself is won over by . . . Joy.

added.title: The Name
added.description: When Mom reveals Gumball's real name is Zach, Gumball adopts a cheesy, annoying persona to match the name. His family tries to make him remember the old Gumball as this new Zach persona is progressively taking over Gumball's life and erasing his memories. If they can't reach him in time, the old Gumball will disappear forever and they'll be left with Zach!

added.title: The Extras
added.description: It's quiet a day for Gumball and Darwin and the background characters finally get their chance to shine. Nothing much is happening for Gumball and Darwin and the background characters in Elmore seize their moment. An array of diverse characters you may have noticed lurking in the background of Gumball and Darwin's adventures finally let their voices be heard. A series of sketches include some tennis crowd extras, two pizzas in love and The Bacon Guy.

added.title: The Gripes
added.description: The kids complain so much they become actual charity cases. Gumball is in such a bad mood that it spreads to Darwin, who joins him in complaining about everything. Their constant moaning grabs the attention of the good people of Elmore. Mistaking Gumball and Darwin for genuine kids in need, they put on a benefit and raise money for them. How do Gumball and Darwin confess there's been a mix-up without inciting a riot?!!

added.title: The Vacation
added.description: The Wattersons set off on a relaxing vacation and end up running for their lives! The Wattersons are swapping scary stories on a family vacation, when their car breaks down in the middle of the desert. They are left with no alternative but to trust a complete stranger, whose appearance matches the scary guy in Mom's story. When the stranger brings them to a derelict gas station, just as he did in mom's made-up scary story, the Wattersons can no longer pretend the story isn't coming true . . .

added.title: The Puppy
added.description: The kids finally get the puppy they always wanted, except . . . it's actually a turtle, and it hates them. After begging Dad for a puppy, the kids are taken aback when he comes home with a turtle. Despite the fact that the turtle turns out to be extremely aggressive (especially toward Gumball) they try their best to give it the love it deserves. This achieves nothing. The Evil Turtle escapes and goes on a rampage, and they have to find it before it destroys Elmore.

added.title: The Recipe
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind Anton's immortality. Anton's little toasty body disintegrates during a swim class. When Gumball and Darwin see Anton the next day, as good as new, they set out to discover his secret. It turns out that his parents use a special formula to bake new Antons when necessary. So the kids test it out at home and end up baking a clone army whose leader - Ant-one - wants to destroy Anton and take over the world.

added.title: The Kids
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's voices may be breaking, but they're showing no signs of growing up. Whilst Gumball and Darwin make fun of Mom and Dad for being old, their voices start to break. They try to ignore it, but everybody they meet reacts to their new and unpredictable voices. Gumball and Darwin finally decide to make the most of their childhood whilst there's still time.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Sarah, the new kid in school, is Gumball and Darwin's number one, slightly obsessive, fan. Sarah is intensely following Gumball and Darwin around trying to win their friendship.  When Gumball tells her that she is acting like a stalker, she embraces it and actually takes it up a notch.  However, when Gumball and Darwin realise that she's behaving this way because she's lonely, they go to surprising lengths to make her feel accepted.

added.title: The Legend of the Library
added.description: When the library is thrown into disarray, an ancient ghost is awoken.

added.title: Locked Out Cold
added.description: On the eve of a big holiday party, the Williams kids are locked out of the house, leading to a frantic search all over town for a spare key.

added.title: Beyond the Overpass
added.description: The Capture the Flag war is over. Craig returns to the Creek, hoping to get some recognition for his heroic deeds, but finds a new quest instead.

added.title: Sink or Swim Team
added.description: Craig offers to help the Sewer Queen by going undercover as a member of the swim team.

added.title: The Quick Name
added.description: Craig tries to rid himself of a bad nickname.

added.title: The Other Side: The Tournament
added.description: The Tournament - Hoping to win a special prize for his Dad's birthday, Craig and his friends compete in a tournament on the Other Side of the Creek!

added.title: The Ground Is Lava!
added.description: When an intense game of "The Ground is Lava" breaks out, Craig must carefully traverse the Creek to save his sister.

added.title: Council of the Creek: Operation Hive-Mind
added.description: Hive Mind - When bees take over the Trading Tree, Craig must assemble the Council of the Creek to avert disaster.

added.title: Pencil Break Mania
added.description: When Pencil Break Mania hits the Creek, JP finds himself as an unlikely champion and is forced to defend his title against the very best!

added.title: The Last Game of Summer
added.description: It's the last day of summer, and the last chance for Craig to uncover an ancient treasure beneath the Creek.

added.title: Creek Shorts
added.description: Craig and his friends demonstrate How to Map the Creek, Craig tries to name every Creek Kid, and more! The Williams Family Intro: Craig imagines what it would be like if his family had a TV Show./How to Map the Creek: Craig shows us how to map the Creek!/Brother Chauffeur: Craig gets to be the ultimate backseat driver./The Kids in the Creek: Craig tries to name every kid in the Creek, but it's easier said than done./Between A Rock: Craig and his friends run afoul of the rock kids.

added.title: Subway
added.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

added.title: Panda's Friend
added.description: Panda uses an app to find a friend with whom he has more common with. Soon things take a turn for the worse when the new friend gets too possessive.
The Baby Bears' dreams come true when they find a 100 dollar bill. But when they can't bear to spend it, they realize it's difficult to let go.

added.title: Neighbors
added.description: Some new neighbors set up camp next to the Bears' cave. Panda and Ice love it, but Grizz thinks they're up to no good.

added.title: Professor Lampwick
added.description: Chloe's professor is too mean to give her any face time to talk over her poor grade. The Bears take things into their own hands to help, causing big trouble for Chloe.

added.title: Ralph
added.description: Charlie meets a creature just like him named Ralph. Charlie loves having a new friend, but the Bears think Ralph is bad news.

added.title: Planet Bears
added.description: A nature documentary follows the Bears through their normal routine, which includes a trip to the grocery store.

added.title: Coffee Cave
added.description: After finding out Ice Bear is a master barista, the Bears turn their cave into a popular coffee shop. But it all goes awry when Ice Bear gets too into coffee and goes berserk.

added.title: Charlie's Big Foot
added.description: After Charlie hurts his foot, The Bears have to sneak him into a hospital for medical assistance.

added.title: The Demon
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.

added.title: Panda's Art
added.description: Panda paints a portrait of Charlie and it's a hit with his art class. But after an art dealer offers to buy the painting, Panda has to get it back from Charlie.

added.title: Poppy Rangers
added.description: Ranger Tabes leads a troop of young girls into a cave expedition, and brings Grizz as their cave expert.

added.title: Lucy's Brother
added.description: To impress Lucy Panda offers to babysit her brother, Clifford. But Clifford turns out to be too high maintenance for Panda to handle.

added.title: The Fair
added.description: The Baby Bears make a deal with a carnival worker to be prizes for a game of ball toss.

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
added.description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

added.title: Stray Bullet
added.description: In order to save an innocent squirrel, Bubbles gives him a dash of Chemical X, giving him some super squirrel powers.

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: Members Only
added.description: When the girls try to join an all-male superhero organization, they learn that sometimes supermen aren't so super.

added.title: Him Diddle Riddle
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls must solve a series of Him's riddles to keep the Professor from having to pay.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Knock It Off
added.description: When the Professor's college roommate sees his old pal's brilliant creations, he decides to cash in on the popularity of the Powerpuffs.

added.title: Power-Noia
added.description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

added.title: Forced Kin
added.description: A terrible, evil menace from outer space descends upon Townville. The girls must fight evil with evil so they seek the advice of Mojo Jojo.

added.title: Superfriends
added.description: The new girl next door learns it's hard to be best friends with superheroes and soon starts hanging out with the wrong kind of kid, Princess.

added.title: All Chalked Up
added.description: Him tricks Bubbles into bringing her chalk drawings to life, who then proceed to wreak havoc in Townsville.

added.title: Helter Shelter/Power Lunch
added.description: Helter Shelter: Bubbles has a habit of saving helpless animals and the Professor is sick of it. When Bubbles brings a baby whale home, she and her sisters have a whale of a time hiding this new addition./Power Lunch: The Gangreen Gang shoplifts from a mini-mart, shoveling loads of food down their throats as fast as possible. When the girls fire at them with their laser vision, a strange reaction occurs.

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: Worship
added.description: When the Fashionistas unveil their new mind controlling perfume, the Powerpuff Girls must find a way to stop them before Townsville falls under their spell.

added.title: Blossom3
added.description: After being blasted by Duplikate, Blossom turns into a triple threat.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Trouble Clef
added.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

added.title: The Last Donnycorn
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

added.title: Green Wing
added.description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

added.title: 15 Minutes of Fame
added.description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Clawdad
added.description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: A Star is Blossom
added.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

added.title: Mini Golf Madness
added.description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

added.title: Summer Bummer
added.description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

added.title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
added.description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Historical Friction
added.description: Steven and Jamie put on a play about the founding of Beach City.

added.title: Friend Ship
added.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: Five Short Graybles
added.description: A series of short stories all centered around the five senses, hosted by Pen Ward himself.

added.title: Web Weirdos
added.description: When Finn gets trapped in a giant spider web, he ends up playing marriage counselor to a couple of grumpy arachnids.

added.title: Dream of Love
added.description: Tree Trunks is courted by an oinking suitor, but much to Jake's dismay, this interferes with her baking habits.

added.title: In Your Footsteps
added.description: A bear befriends Finn and Jake, but what are his true intentions?

added.title: Hot to the Touch
added.description: Finn goes on a quest to prove Flame Princess isn't really evil.

added.title: The Monster
added.description: Lumpy Space Princess's parents have come to ask Finn and Jake to find their daughter and convince her to come home.

added.title: Still
added.description: Finn and Jake find themselves paralyzed from the neck down and at the Ice King's mercy!

added.title: Wizard Battle
added.description: Every couple hundred of years or so, all the wizards in Ooo assemble for Wizard Sport, a fantastic, wizards-only battle royale.

added.title: Adventure Time with Fionna and Cake
added.description: It's a parallel universe where we explore the adventures of Fiona and Cake from the land of Aaa!

added.title: What Was Missing
added.description: Finn and Jake do battle with a powerful door lord.

added.title: Laundry Woes
added.description: Mordecai wants to return Margaret's sweater to her.

added.title: Silver Dude
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to make money for a video game by street performing.

added.title: Benson's Car
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix Benson's car before he finds out they broke its window.

added.title: Every Meat Burritos
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

added.title: Wall Buddy
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to clean up their room.

added.title: Starter Pack
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to stop Muscle Man from messing with Thomas.

added.title: Payback/Party Bus
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Wallpaper Man
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: 150-Piece Kit
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he performed a famous drum solo.

added.title: Bald Spot
added.description: Muscle Man wants to hide his bald spot at all costs.

added.title: Guy's Night
added.description: Pops wants to beat the milk challenge to prove he's one of the guys.

added.title: One Pull Up
added.description: Rigby needs to do one pull-up so he can pass the park physical.

added.title: T.G.I. Tuesday
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby and Eileen want to celebrate Margaret's new internship before she has to quit the coffee shop.

added.title: Firework Run
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby and Muscle Man have to get fireworks for an event at the park because they used the ones Benson got.

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Field Trippin'
added.description: After a pit stop bathroom break during a school field trip, Clarence returns to the parking lot and accidentally gets on the wrong school bus - which takes him to a different school!

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: The Tails of Mardrynia
added.description: After reading a book about a mystical animal society in class, Clarence is inspired to round up local animals and recreate an animal world of his own to cheer up his friend Percy. But will Percy take the game too far?

added.title: The Little Mer-Tiger
added.description: The origin of Tiger is told as a flashback.  As the legend goes, Tiger used to be a mermaid.  One day the evil ruler of the sea, Bubble Grandpa, demanded a hamburger and picked Tiger to retrieve it.  He used his magic sea powers to give Tiger legs and send her ashore.  But Tiger grew to love the land, and with the help of her new friend, Uncle Grandpa, defeated the evil sea ruler and got to keep her legs.

added.title: Ballroom
added.description: MG fixes up the ballroom and warns UG and PS not to step a foot in there until he gets a chance to use it.  But UG mistakenly tosses a ball into the room.  Now PS and UG have to retrieve the ball without touching one foot to the ground.

added.title: Back to the Library
added.description: Uncle Grandpa uses time travel to convince his past self to return a library book on time.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Numbskull
added.description: A head Injury turns Mr. Gus into a bumbling fools whose wacky antics make him Uncle Grandpa's coolest friend. No longer the focus of Uncle Grandpa's attention, a jealous Pizza Steve tries to desperately to get back normal. Mr. Gus has to restore social balance in the RV.

added.title: Body Trouble
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Belly Bag have a disagreement, they separate and try to make each other jealous.

added.title: Shower Party
added.description: Things get out of hand when Andrew W. K. helps Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus throw a party while Uncle Grandpa is in the shower.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Land
added.description: Pizza Steve must find a way to sneak onto his own roller coaster at the newly opened Uncle Grandpa Land.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's number one fan gets more than he bargained for when Uncle Grandpa overstays his welcome.

added.title: The Package
added.description: The gang gets nutty after repeatedly failing to open a mysterious package.

added.title: Are You Talking to Tree?
added.description: When the tree inside the RV begins talking to Uncle Grandpa, he must convince the gang that he's not going crazy.

added.title: Older
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa mistakenly transforms a young boy into a three-hundred-year-old man, he must manage to turn the kid back to normal before anyone gets hurt.

added.title: Guest Directed Shorts
added.description: A showcase of three Uncle Grandpa shorts presented in three unique animation styles.
